			 May 2004<br>
<br>
In this issue:
<p>1. Introducing: The SimpleNet Site of the Month!<br>
  2. Our Partner: JimWorld Johnny&#8217;s Ramblings<br>
  3. The SimpleNet Referral Program<br>
  4. Why SimpleNet? Clustering, and why you need it!<br>
  5. What&#8217;s Cool this Month?<br>
  6. Send Us Feedback!</p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  1. Introducing: The SimpleNet Site of the Month</p>
<p>Some of the coolest sites on the Internet are found on SimpleNet. And now,
  we&#8217;re going to show them to you!<br>
  Each month we&#8217;ll choose a new SimpleNet site for:</p>
<p>-	Placement on the SimpleNet.com home page and login<br>
  -	Your own Site of the Month page on our site<br>
  -	Inclusion in our monthly newsletter</p>
<p>How do you sign up? Simply visit our Site of the Month page and add your site
  to the list of sites to be reviewed, read the terms and sign up! To sign up
  now:</p>
<p>SimpleNet Site of the Month: May 2004<br>
  <a href="http://www.clusterfunction.com"><br>
  http://www.clusterfunction.com</a></p>
<p>ClusterFunction.com is an amalgamation of many strange and wonderful (and
  some not so wonderful) (no)things that are found on the Internet, plus the
  scattered musings from its creator&#8230;</p>
<p>To check out the Site of the Month, please visit:<br>
  <a href="http://www.simplenet.com/som">http://www.simplenet.com/som</a></p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  2. JimWorld: A Resource for Web Site Owners<br>
  An excerpt from the JimWorld Gazette&#8230;</p>
<p>Johnny&#8217;s SEO Tip&#8230;<br>
  I still get tons of email from people asking me what SEO keyword stuffing software
    works best, wondering why they have &#8220;my search page&#8221; on their
    site 300 times, yet no search engine puts them in the top 10. Start by describing
    your products and/or services in actual, readable text that humans with an
    elementary reading level can understand and use your keyword phrases in your
    descriptions to describe them. Consider this example, &#8220;XYZ Product,
    the premier office cleaning solution, at $9.99 per bottle, will make cleaning
    your office much easier due to its concentrated power. Because it&#8217;s
    concentrated, XYZ Office cleaning solution makes great financial sense because
    a little goes a long way.&#8221; That description is easy to read, has all
    the necessary keywords and phrases, and is much better than saying, &#8220;Office
    cleaning solution product XYZ is the best office cleaning solution you can
    buy to clean your office.&#8221; What does that say? Nothing!</p>
<p>For more tips on SEO optimization and other resources, please visit our partner,
  JimWorld. Archives of their newsletter can be found online at:<br>
  <a href="http://www.jimworld.com/gazette">http://www.jimworld.com/gazette</a></p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  3. The SimpleNet Referral Program</p>
<p>The SimpleNet Referral Program allows you to earn credit towards you current
  account balance by referring your family, friends, and associates to SimpleNet.
  For each new web site account that is referred to us, you will receive one
  FREE month of service on your existing account (up to $35)! The more new accounts
  that you refer, the more FREE months you will receive.</p>
<p>To learn more about the Referral Program, please visit:<br>
  <a href="http://simplenet.com/referral.html">http://simplenet.com/referral.html</a></p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  4. Why SimpleNet? Clustering, and why you need it!</p>
<p>By clustering multiple servers and connections together in our Data Center,
  we can create a highly available and reliable system. Clustering is used for
  traffic load-balancing across several servers and to prevent the failure of
  the platform by allowing access to continue even if one server goes offline.<br>
  How does this relate to your web site? Clustering helps assure that it will
  not go offline and, therefore, render your site inaccessible. It also assists
  in making sure that traffic gets to your site as fast as possible by measuring
  the work load of multiple web servers and distributing requests to the least
  busy machine.<br>
  Our clustered, redundant, reliable, and revolutionary web hosting platform
  is the only home for your site.</p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  5. What&#8217;s Cool this Month?</p>
<p>We, at SimpleNet, spend all day on the &#8216;net, so why wouldn&#8217;t we
  tell you about some of the crazy stuff that we encounter? Well, here ya go!
  Each month we&#8217;ll show you something that we&#8217;ve found that we think
  is totally cool. Enjoy!</p>
<p>communimage is a collaborative art project since 1999. Thousands of people
  have contributed to a growing sea of images. communimage is an attempt to entertain
  a visual global dialogue.</p>
<p>Check it out:<br>
  <a href="http://www.communimage.ch/engl/">http://www.communimage.ch/engl/</a></p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  6. We want to hear from you!</p>
<p>The best way for us to bring you the services that you need is for you to
  tell us what you want! Whether it be to talk about our support, suggest new
  services or just tell us that we are doing a great job, please use our feedback
  areas as often as you like!</p>
<p>How do you do that?<br>
  1. Reply to this email<br>
  OR<br>
  2. Use our feedback form, located at:<br>
  <a href="http://www.simplenet.com/contact.html">http://www.simplenet.com/contact.html</a></p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>Thanks for reading and for being a SimpleNet customer!</p>
<p>Best wishes,<br>
  The SimpleNet Team</p>
<p>For assistance, please contact Customer Service:<br>
  <a href="http://simplenet.com/contact.html">http://simplenet.com/contact.html</a></p>
<p>SimpleNet takes your privacy seriously. To learn more,<br>
  please read our privacy policy, located at<br>
  <a href="http://www.simplenet.com/privacy.html">http://www.simplenet.com/privacy.html</a><br>
</p>			  
